---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts';

const pageTitle = `Notion AI vs Grammarly: Which AI Writing Tool Wins in 2026? — ${SITE_TITLE}`;
const pageDescription = 'We compared Notion AI and Grammarly to find the best AI writing assistant in 2026. Read our hands-on review, feature comparison, and final recommendation.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} />
		<style>
			.review-wrap {
				max-width: 760px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 40px 24px;
				min-height: calc(100vh - 200px);
			}
			.review-wrap h1 {
				font-size: 2.2em;
				margin-bottom: 12px;
				line-height: 1.2;
			}
			.meta {
				font-size: 14px;
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				margin-bottom: 28px;
			}
			.intro {
				font-size: 18px;
				line-height: 1.8;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
				margin-bottom: 32px;
				padding-bottom: 24px;
				border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
			}
			.review-wrap h2 {
				font-size: 1.5em;
				margin-top: 40px;
				margin-bottom: 16px;
				color: rgb(var(--black));
			}
			.review-wrap h3 {
				font-size: 1.2em;
				margin-top: 28px;
				margin-bottom: 12px;
				color: rgb(var(--black));
			}
			.review-wrap p,
			.review-wrap li {
				font-size: 17px;
				line-height: 1.8;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
			}
			.review-wrap ul {
				margin-bottom: 16px;
				padding-left: 24px;
			}
			.review-wrap li {
				margin-bottom: 8px;
			}
			.review-wrap a {
				color: var(--accent);
				text-decoration: underline;
			}
			.compare-table {
				width: 100%;
				border-collapse: collapse;
				margin: 20px 0 32px 0;
				font-size: 15px;
			}
			.compare-table th,
			.compare-table td {
				padding: 12px 14px;
				border: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
				text-align: left;
			}
			.compare-table th {
				background: rgb(var(--gray-light));
				font-weight: 600;
				color: rgb(var(--black));
			}
			.compare-table td {
				background: var(--card-bg);
			}
			.compare-table tr:nth-child(even) td {
				background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.4);
			}
			.winner-box,
			.runner-box,
			.budget-box {
				border-radius: 12px;
				padding: 24px;
				margin-bottom: 16px;
			}
			.winner-box {
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1), rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.05));
				border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.3);
			}
			.runner-box {
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(92, 124, 255, 0.1), rgba(92, 124, 255, 0.05));
				border: 1px solid rgba(92, 124, 255, 0.3);
			}
			.budget-box {
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.1), rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.05));
				border: 1px solid rgba(245, 166, 35, 0.3);
			}
			.winner-box h3,
			.runner-box h3,
			.budget-box h3 {
				margin-top: 0;
				font-size: 18px;
			}
			.winner-box h3 { color: #22c55e; }
			.runner-box h3 { color: var(--accent); }
			.budget-box h3 { color: #f5a623; }
			.pick-label {
				display: inline-block;
				font-size: 12px;
				font-weight: 700;
				text-transform: uppercase;
				letter-spacing: 0.5px;
				padding: 4px 10px;
				border-radius: 6px;
				margin-bottom: 8px;
			}
			.winner-box .pick-label { background: #22c55e; color: white; }
			.runner-box .pick-label { background: var(--accent); color: white; }
			.budget-box .pick-label { background: #f5a623; color: white; }
			.cta-inline {
				display: inline-flex;
				align-items: center;
				gap: 6px;
				padding: 10px 20px;
				background: var(--accent);
				color: white;
				font-weight: 600;
				border-radius: 8px;
				text-decoration: none;
				margin-top: 8px;
				transition: all 0.2s ease;
			}
			.cta-inline:hover {
				background: var(--accent-dark);
				transform: translateY(-1px);
			}
			.faq-item {
				margin-bottom: 20px;
			}
			.faq-item h4 {
				font-size: 17px;
				margin-bottom: 6px;
				color: rgb(var(--black));
			}
			.faq-item p {
				margin: 0;
			}
			@media (max-width: 720px) {
				.review-wrap {
					padding: 32px 16px;
				}
				.review-wrap h1 {
					font-size: 1.7em;
				}
				.compare-table {
					font-size: 13px;
				}
				.compare-table th,
				.compare-table td {
					padding: 10px;
				}
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<div class="review-wrap">
			<h1>Notion AI vs Grammarly: Which AI Writing Tool Wins in 2026?</h1>
			<p class="meta">Published May 19, 2026 · AI Writing · 6 min read</p>

			<p class="intro">
				AI writing tools have transformed how we create content — but not all assistants are built the same. <strong>Notion AI</strong> embeds artificial intelligence directly into your notes and documents, while <strong>Grammarly</strong> focuses obsessively on grammar, clarity, and tone across every app you use. If you are deciding between these two popular tools, the answer depends entirely on how you write. Let us break it down.
			</p>

			<h2>Quick Comparison</h2>
			<table class="compare-table">
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>Feature</th>
						<th>Notion AI</th>
						<th>Grammarly</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td><strong>Free Plan</strong></td>
						<td>Limited (included in Notion free)</td>
						<td>Grammar & spelling only</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td><strong>Paid Plan</strong></td>
						<td>$10/user/month (Notion AI add-on)</td>
						<td>$12/month (Premium)</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td><strong>Core Strength</strong></td>
						<td>Content generation & summarization</td>
						<td>Grammar, tone, & clarity checking</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td><strong>Integration</strong></td>
						<td>Inside Notion workspace only</td>
						<td>Browser, email, Office, mobile keyboard</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td><strong>Works Offline</strong></td>
						<td>Partially</td>
						<td>Desktop app only</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td><strong>Plagiarism Check</strong></td>
						<td>No</td>
						<td>Yes (Premium)</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td><strong>Team Collaboration</strong></td>
						<td>Excellent (built into Notion)</td>
						<td>Business plan only</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td><strong>Our Rating</strong></td>
						<td>★★★★☆ 4.7</td>
						<td>★★★★☆ 4.5</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>

			<h2>Notion AI Review</h2>
			<p>
				Notion AI is not a standalone writing tool — it is an intelligence layer built into the Notion workspace you already use. This integration is both its greatest strength and its biggest limitation. When you are inside Notion, the AI can do remarkable things: summarize a 5,000-word research document into bullet points, generate a blog post outline from a single sentence, translate meeting notes into Spanish, or extract action items from a chaotic brainstorming session.
			</p>
			<p>
				The magic comes from context. Because Notion AI lives inside your workspace, it can reference your existing databases, project docs, and wikis when generating content. Ask it to "write a project brief using the requirements from our Q3 Roadmap doc" and it actually understands what you mean. For teams already using Notion as their central knowledge hub, this contextual awareness is unmatched by any standalone writing assistant.
			</p>

			<h3>Pros</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Deep workspace integration</strong> — The AI understands your existing notes, databases, and documents, producing contextual drafts that reference real data.</li>
				<li><strong>All-in-one productivity</strong> — No need to switch apps. Brainstorm, draft, edit, and publish from the same workspace your team already uses.</li>
				<li><strong>Powerful summarization</strong> — Turn lengthy docs into bullet points, extract key decisions from meeting notes, and generate FAQs automatically.</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Cons</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Locked to Notion</strong> — If you write in Google Docs, Word, or email clients, Notion AI cannot help you. It is Notion-only.</li>
				<li><strong>Grammar checking is basic</strong> — It catches obvious errors but lacks the depth of Grammarly's tone, clarity, and engagement analysis.</li>
			</ul>

			<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Notion power users, project teams, and content creators who want AI assistance inside a unified workspace. If your life already lives in Notion, this is a no-brainer.</p>

			<a href="[AFFILIATE_LINK_NOTION_AI]" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cta-inline">
				Try Notion AI Free →
			</a>

			<h2>Grammarly Review</h2>
			<p>
				Grammarly has spent over a decade perfecting one thing: making your writing clear, correct, and compelling. With over 30 million daily users, it is the most widely deployed writing assistant in the world — and for good reason. Unlike Notion AI, which generates content, Grammarly acts as a vigilant editor that follows you everywhere: Gmail, Twitter, LinkedIn, Slack, Microsoft Word, and even your phone's keyboard.
			</p>
			<p>
				The Premium plan elevates Grammarly from a spell-checker to a genuine writing coach. It does not just flag grammar errors; it analyzes your sentence structure for clarity, suggests vocabulary enhancements to avoid repetition, detects passive voice, evaluates your tone (formal vs. casual vs. friendly), and even checks for plagiarism against billions of web pages. For non-native English speakers, the tone detector alone is worth the subscription price.
			</p>

			<h3>Pros</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Works everywhere you write</strong> — Browser extension, desktop app, mobile keyboard, and Office plugin cover virtually every writing surface.</li>
				<li><strong>Advanced tone and clarity analysis</strong> — Goes beyond grammar to evaluate how your writing will land with readers.</li>
				<li><strong>Plagiarism detection</strong> — Premium users can check documents against 16 billion web pages, essential for academics and journalists.</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Cons</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Cannot generate content</strong> — Grammarly is purely an editor. It will not write your first draft or summarize a document for you.</li>
				<li><strong>Occasionally over-suggests</strong> — The AI sometimes recommends changes that strip personality from your writing, making everything sound generic.</li>
			</ul>

			<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Professionals, students, non-native English speakers, and anyone who writes across multiple apps and platforms. If you want an editor that follows you everywhere, Grammarly is unmatched.</p>

			<a href="[AFFILIATE_LINK_GRAMMARLY]" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cta-inline">
				Try Grammarly Free →
			</a>

			<h2>Our Editor's Picks</h2>

			<div class="winner-box">
				<span class="pick-label">Winner</span>
				<h3>🏆 Grammarly — Best Overall</h3>
				<p>
					For most writers, Grammarly delivers more daily value. Its universal availability means it improves every email, tweet, and report you write — not just the ones inside Notion. The tone analysis and plagiarism checker are genuinely professional-grade features that justify the subscription.
				</p>
				<a href="[AFFILIATE_LINK_GRAMMARLY]" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cta-inline">
					Get Grammarly Premium →
				</a>
			</div>

			<div class="runner-box">
				<span class="pick-label">Runner Up</span>
				<h3>🥈 Notion AI — Best for Teams</h3>
				<p>
					If your team already uses Notion, the AI add-on is transformative. Summarizing meeting notes, generating project briefs from databases, and translating docs without leaving your workspace saves hours every week. The contextual awareness is something Grammarly simply cannot match.
				</p>
				<a href="[AFFILIATE_LINK_NOTION_AI]" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cta-inline">
					Try Notion AI →
				</a>
			</div>

			<div class="budget-box">
				<span class="pick-label">Budget Pick</span>
				<h3>💰 Grammarly Free — Best Free Option</h3>
				<p>
					Grammarly's free tier catches spelling, grammar, and basic punctuation errors across all your apps. For casual writers, it provides 80% of the value at zero cost. Upgrade to Premium only when you need tone analysis, plagiarism checks, or vocabulary suggestions.
				</p>
				<a href="[AFFILIATE_LINK_GRAMMARLY]" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="cta-inline">
					Get Grammarly Free →
				</a>
			</div>

			<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h4>Can I use both Notion AI and Grammarly together?</h4>
				<p>
					Absolutely — and many writers do. Use Notion AI to generate first drafts, brainstorm ideas, and summarize research inside Notion. Then copy the finished draft into Grammarly (via the browser extension or desktop app) for final grammar, tone, and clarity polishing before publishing.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h4>Is Grammarly Premium worth the $12/month?</h4>
				<p>
					For professional writers, students, and non-native English speakers, yes. The tone detector, vocabulary enhancement, and plagiarism checker are features you will use daily. Casual writers can get by with the free tier indefinitely. Grammarly often runs 40% off promotions for annual subscriptions.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="faq-item">
				<h4>Does Notion AI require a paid Notion plan?</h4>
				<p>
					Notion AI is a paid add-on ($10/user/month) on top of any Notion plan, including the free plan. However, every Notion workspace gets a limited number of free AI responses to test the feature. The AI add-on is available for both free and paid Notion plans — it is not included in Notion Plus or Business by default.
				</p>
			</div>

			<p style="margin-top: 40px; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(var(--gray));">
				<em>Disclosure: This review contains affiliate links. We may earn a commission if you purchase through these links, at no extra cost to you. All opinions are our own based on hands-on testing.</em>
			</p>
		</div>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
